<p>Newer developments in areas like Hardin Valley and Farragut typically feature more modern construction with better insulation and optimal roof orientations for solar panels. These neighborhoods often have HOA guidelines regarding solar installations, though Tennessee law prohibits unreasonable restrictions on solar panels. In downtown areas like the Old City, urban heat island effects can increase cooling costs, making high-efficiency HVAC systems particularly valuable. Suburban neighborhoods like Powell and Halls offer excellent solar potential with fewer shading concerns and typically have the roof space needed for larger solar arrays that can completely offset home energy usage.</p>

